# Release Process — TelegramAutoDownload

## MANDATORY: Every release MUST include both files

Every `gh release create` or `gh release upload` command **must** include:

1. `TelegramAutoDownload_vX.X.X_Setup.exe` — Inno Setup installer (for installed users + new installs)
2. `TelegramAutoDownload_vX.X.X_Portable.zip` — ZIP archive (for portable users)

## Steps for each release

```powershell
# 1. Bump version in AppVersion.cs and setup.iss
# 2. Publish
dotnet publish TelegramAutoDownload/TelegramAutoDownload.csproj -c Release -r win-x64 --self-contained true -p:PublishSingleFile=true -o publish/

# 3. Create ZIP
Compress-Archive -Path publish/* -DestinationPath "TelegramAutoDownload_vX.X.X_Portable.zip" -Force

# 4. Compile installer (REQUIRED — never skip)
& "C:\InnoSetup\ISCC.exe" installer/setup.iss

# 5. Release with BOTH files (never release with only one)
gh release create vX.X.X "TelegramAutoDownload_vX.X.X_Portable.zip" "TelegramAutoDownload_vX.X.X_Setup.exe" --title "vX.X.X" --notes "..."
```

## Never do

- ❌ Release with only ZIP and no Setup.exe
- ❌ Delete Setup.exe from a release to "fix" update issues — fix the code instead
- ❌ Skip the Inno Setup compile step
